Package Consommable

Class FoodItem

java.lang.Object
Consommable.FoodItem
Direct Known Subclasses:
BeetrootJuice, Boar, carrot, FairlyFreshFish, FourLeafCloverNotFresh, FreshFourLeafClover, HairFromIdefix, Honey, Lobster, Mead, MilkFromATwoHeadedUnicorn, Mistletoe, RockOil, Salt, SecretIngredient, StaleFish, Strawberries, Wine
public class FoodItem extends Object
Represents a consumable food item in the simulation. It holds nutritional values, freshness status, and categories.

    • FoodItem

      public FoodItem(String name, Freshness freshness, int hungerLevel, int healthDelta, int belligerence, int strengthDelta, int enduranceDelta, FoodCategory... cats)
      Constructs a new FoodItem with specific properties.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the food.
      freshness - The initial freshness state.
      hungerLevel - The amount of hunger this item satisfies.
      healthDelta - The effect on health (positive or negative).
      belligerence - The effect on belligerence.
      strengthDelta - The temporary bonus to strength.
      enduranceDelta - The temporary bonus to endurance.
      cats - Variable arguments listing the categories this food belongs to.

      public boolean isFresh()
      Checks if the food is considered edible and fresh.
      Returns:
      true if the food is FRESH or FAIRLYFRESH, false if STALE.

    • getCategories

      public List<FoodCategory> getCategories()
      Retrieves the list of categories associated with this item. Necessary for applying dietary rules (e.g., the vegetable rule).
      Returns:
      A list of FoodCategory.

    • rot

      public void rot()
      Simulates the natural decay of the food item. Reduces the freshness level (e.g., FRESH -> FAIRLYFRESH -> STALE).
